title: Wall Street Journal Saturday 9 June 2018
description:
Happy to help out!

I would have to agree that this place has become wanked. I could be 
keeping a list of the vomit clowns that post voluminously every day
in amounts that they cannot possibly service in any reasonable amount
of time, not to mention the complete lack of description, and my
personal favorite is the gigabyte zip file with no listing of the
contents. Yes, I could be keeping a list and checking it twice but 
the fact is that if you can't be bothered then neither can I because 
it's just junk to pump up your numbers with. And that reminds me I 
have to delete my collection of 437 how-to and how-big and how-hard
is your penis ebooks.
Enough with the negative though. This is a time when history is being
made. Our president (ya-fired!) is about to begin a meeting whose 
outcome will have global consequences. Yes, that's right, this is the
beginning of the end of N Korea. In 5 years that peninnsula will be 
completely paved over in Big-Mac cartons and styrofoam take-out 
containers, no house will be worth less than a million bucks, all
forested areas will be thinned into parkland and the native wildlife
will have been relocated to zoo's. Ah, the stink of civilization. I 
can only say... don't do it Kim! Press that button now and preserve
the simple uncluttered way of living. Death to twitter,
and #me-too...
woops, too much positive energy there.

Notch Johnson just saying,
Ride the big one.


 Wall Street Journal Saturday-Sunday 09-10 June 2018
